content.description: This is the tiny route on the arete of one of the boulders in the mini Atom Smasher-esqe cluster at the SE corner of the Cheyenne Social Club. Start in the chimney and have at it. Although this route is tiny the move is somewhat tricky. There are nice caves with shade at the base here.

climbs.name: The Little Man in the Boat
climbs.fa: Todd Gordon, Tucker Tech, Tom Burke

content.description: This route starts in a slightly overhanging crack with a bolt to clip right off the ground. Grab the Little Man (a flake) and pull into the crack. Be gentle with the little guy as he is loose. Climb the crack over a bulge and climb the fun lieback flake above. The descent is a little tricky (start by dropping off towards the Pencil) but no "convenience" anchor is necessary.

climbs.name: [Redacted]
climbs.fa: Todd Gordon, Tucker Tech, Tom Burke

content.description: If one is standing near the route "Win Dixie" and looking up at the hillside this route is at the top of the hill. It starts in a left facing dihedral with fairly rotten rock to a ledge. Clip the first of 4 bolts which protect the crux stemming. Pass a knob and stand on top. The belay / lower off point is two 3/8" bolts with runners to extend to the lip. The route "The Little Man In the Boat" is just left of the start.

climbs.name: [Redacted]
climbs.fa: Todd Gordon, Dave Evans, Tucker Tech

content.description: This route is halfway up the hill from Win Dixie on a south facing slab. Climb and clip past 4 bolts to a 2 bolt anchor. A good first lead for someone in the 5.7 zone.
